					<description><!--[CDATA[<p-->A hysterectomy can treat many gynecologic conditions, including fibroids, painful periods and cancer, such as&nbsp;endometrial,&nbsp;cervical,&nbsp;ovarian&nbsp;and uterine cancers. Dr. Megan Wasson,&nbsp;a gynecologic surgeon at Mayo Clinic, specializes in&nbsp;minimally invasive surgery. She says the decision to undergo a hysterectomy is highly individualized, based on each patient's specific needs.&nbsp; In many cases, a minimally invasive approach is an […]<p></p>
